<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Zingiberaceae" genus="Hanguana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hanguana loi" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="loi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Hanguana loi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mohd Fahmi, Sofiman Othman &amp; P.C.Boyce but differs in flat leaf blade (vs corrugated), pseudopetioles 0.8-2.1 cm wide (vs to 0.6 cm wide), rachis of infructescence up to 10 cm long (vs ca 58 cm long), ripe fruit ca 1 cm in diam. (vs ca 0.5 cm in diam.), and unbranched partial infructescences (vs branched).
</paragraph>
